#!N  #!Rtall316 Setting the Camera Width 
#!N #!N #!N If you select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Orthographic #!EF projection, then 
you can also specify the width of the field of view. 
The larger the width, the smaller the object appears. #!N #!N 
Specify the width by clicking on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Camera Width #!EF 
field, typing a new value (in world coordinates), and pressing the 
Enter key. #!N #!N While you are using perspective projection, the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Width #!EF field is grayed out. #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   
